  "cover": "https://pulseagent.io/images/blog/hermes-v2026-5-16-cover.png",
  "content": "# Hermes Agent v2026.5.16: Foundation Release Adds LINE + 180x Faster Browser — What Changes for b2b-sdr-agent Skill\n\nHermes Agent v2026.5.16 — dubbed \"The Foundation Release\" — landed on May 16, 2026, delivering 808 commits, 633 merged PRs, and 545 closed issues since v0.13.0. For teams running the **b2b-sdr-agent skill** on [PulseAgent](https://pulseagent.io/app/login?ref=blog&utm_source=blog&utm_medium=release-post&utm_campaign=hermes-v2026.5.16), the headline news is a new messaging channel, dramatic speed improvements, and zero breaking changes.\n\n## What's New in Hermes v2026.5.16\n\n### LINE Messaging API — Channel #4 for East Asian Markets\n\nHermes now natively supports LINE, the dominant messaging platform in Japan, Taiwan, Thailand, Vietnam, and Indonesia. With 22 supported messaging platforms total, this expands your SDR's reach into East Asia without any third-party bridge. Pairing is a single command: `hermes line`.\n\nFor B2B export businesses targeting East Asian buyers, LINE consistently outperforms email on open rates. Japanese procurement teams and Taiwanese traders are significantly more reachable via LINE than cold email.\n\n### 180x Faster Browser Automation\n\nBrowser CDP (Chrome DevTools Protocol) calls now run over a persistent WebSocket connection instead of establishing a new connection per call. For SDR workflows involving web-based lead research — scraping import/export directories, enriching company profiles, verifying contact details — this is a genuine speed multiplier on every research task.\n\n### 19-Second Cold Start Improvement\n\nDeferred imports cut cold-start time by approximately 19 seconds. If your SDR agent runs on a cron schedule — lead discovery every 10 hours, stalled-lead checks every weekday morning — each triggered session now starts nearly half a minute faster. Over dozens of daily invocations, this compounds into real operational efficiency.\n\n### Cross-Session 1-Hour Claude Prompt Caching\n\nPrompt cache now persists for one hour across sessions. For agents with large system prompts (like the full b2b-sdr-agent SKILL.md), repeat invocations within the same hour share cached context — reducing both latency and token costs on every cron trigger.\n\n### PyPI Distribution: One-Command Install\n\nHermes now ships on PyPI, replacing the previous install process:\n\n```bash\npip install hermes-agent\nhermes skills install b2b-sdr-agent\n# or via npx:\nnpx hermes-agent skills install b2b-sdr-agent\n```\n\n### Supply-Chain Advisory Checker\n\nHermes now scans skill dependencies at install time and flags known advisories. If you run custom skill forks or have pinned older dependencies, expect a new advisory output step during install.\n\n### Security Hardening\n\nThree dangerous-command bypasses were closed, sudo brute-force blocking was added, and tool error sanitization now prevents injection via crafted error messages. The b2b-sdr-agent's built-in prompt injection defense runs on a more robust underlying framework as a result.\n\n## b2b-sdr-hermes-skill Compat Audit\n\nWe audited `SKILL.md`, `cron/sdr-schedules.yaml`, and `examples/` against the v2026.5.16 changelog.\n\n| Category | Count | Finding |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| BREAKING | 0 | No renamed APIs, no removed functions |\n| RELEVANT | 2 | LINE channel live; gateway circuit breaker improves channel reliability |\n| WATCH | 3 | MS Teams, SimpleX Chat (new channels); supply-chain scanner (install-time only) |\n| SKIP | rest | Browser CDP internals, LSP diagnostics, Windows beta, xAI/NovitaAI providers |\n\n**SKILL.md Stage 10** already references the LINE channel with the correct setup command (`hermes line`) and target countries (`JP, TW, TH, VN, ID`). This was a forward-compatible annotation added during v2026.5.7 planning — no patch required.\n\n**`cron/sdr-schedules.yaml`** — no changes needed. The cron API surface is unchanged in v2026.5.16.\n\n**`WHATSAPP_ALLOW_STRANGERS=true`** (introduced v2026.5.7) — still required for cold outreach to new contacts. No regression in v2026.5.16.\n\n**Skill version**: b2b-sdr-agent v1.0.0 is fully compatible with Hermes v0.14.0 (2026.5.16).\n\n## Recommended User Action: Upgrade When Ready\n\n**Verdict: No breaking changes. Upgrade on your next maintenance window.**\n\nThe LINE channel is the standout win for any operator targeting East Asian buyers. If your export business reaches Japan, Taiwan, Thailand, Vietnam, or Indonesia — upgrade now and run `hermes line` to pair. Route leads where `country ∈ {JP, TW, TH, VN, ID}` to LINE as the primary channel for measurably higher engagement.\n\nFor everyone else, the 19-second cold-start improvement and cross-session prompt caching are compelling performance reasons to upgrade. There is no rollback risk: the skill's cron schedules, WhatsApp configuration, CRM integrations, and multi-touch outreach sequences all run unchanged on v2026.5.16.\n\n## Install / Upgrade Commands\n\n```bash\n# Fresh install (Hermes + skill)\npip install hermes-agent\nhermes skills install b2b-sdr-agent\n\n# Upgrade existing Hermes\npip install --upgrade hermes-agent\n\n# After upgrade: pair LINE (East Asia markets)\nhermes line\n\n# Verify\nhermes version\n# Expected: Hermes Agent v0.14.0 (2026.5.16)\n```\n\nPin your version in `requirements.txt`:\n\n```\nhermes-agent==0.14.0\n```\n\n## Run Your B2B SDR on Managed Infrastructure\n\nUpgrading Hermes, keeping the WhatsApp session alive, managing cron schedules across timezones — this is real operational overhead for a solo exporter. **[PulseAgent](https://pulseagent.io/app/login?ref=blog&utm_source=blog&utm_medium=release-post&utm_campaign=hermes-v2026.5.16)** hosts the b2b-sdr-agent skill for you:\n\n- Hermes version upgrades happen automatically\n- LINE pairing is done through the dashboard UI\n- Cron schedules run on enterprise-grade infrastructure with guaranteed uptime\n- Multi-tenant isolation keeps your leads and CRM data private\n\n→ [Start free on PulseAgent](https://pulseagent.io/app/login?ref=blog&utm_source=blog&utm_medium=release-post&utm_campaign=hermes-v2026.5.16)\n→ [See pricing](https://pulseagent.io/pricing?ref=blog&utm_source=blog&utm_medium=release-post&utm_campaign=hermes-v2026.5.16)\n→ [AI SDR for B2B Export](https://pulseagent.io/solutions/ai-sdr-for-b2b-export)\n→ [WhatsApp Sales Automation](https://pulseagent.io/solutions/whatsapp-sales-automation)\n→ [Multi-Channel Sales Pipeline](https://pulseagent.io/solutions/multi-channel-sales-pipeline)\n\n---\n\n*Hermes Agent is maintained by NousResearch. The b2b-sdr-agent skill is independently built and maintained by PulseAgent. Version compatibility is tracked at [github.com/ipythoning/b2b-sdr-hermes-skill](https://github.com/ipythoning/b2b-sdr-hermes-skill).*"
